    "created_at": "2025-05-17T10:06:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-05-17T11:18:39Z",
    "body": "**Edit**: oh [I can see here](https://starship.rs/advanced-config/#style-strings) that colors can be set to `prev_fg` and `prev_bg` which sets to the color of the previous element so that could solve that problem actually. I think `next_fg` and `next_bg` would be necessary, though.\n\nI think it'd be better that, rather than a spacer module, every module have a default `start_separator` and ` end_separator` with the ability for the separator to adopt either the foreground or the background color or the module. It would make it easier to design color schemes with backgroun colors like [Gruvbox Rainbow](https://starship.rs/presets/gruvbox-rainbow) and make it work with module that can adopt different background color based on contect like [username](https://starship.rs/config/#username) that can adopt a different background color for `root` or regular user.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
